The PITT code has been used to model the nonlinear generation of waveforms by scattering off a Schwarzschild black hole [228, 229]. The physical setup is similar to the perturbative study in Section 3.7. A radially compact pulse is prescribed on an early time outgoing null hypersurface \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
