Later, a global, characteristic, numerical study of the self-gravitating version of this problem, by Gómez and Winicour, confirmed that the use of the true null cones is essential in getting the correct radiated waveform [109]. For quasi-periodic radiation, the phase of the waveform is particular sensitive to the truncation of the outer region at a finite boundary. Although a perturbative estimate would indicate an \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
