In the CCM strategy, illustrated in Figure 6, the interior black hole region is evolved using an ingoing null algorithm whose inner boundary is a marginally trapped surface, and whose outer boundary lies outside the black hole and forms the inner boundary of a region evolved by the Cauchy algorithm. In turn, the outer boundary of the Cauchy region is handled by matching to an outgoing null evolution extending to \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
